2
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:28,630
First, before going further, let's look at how this is rendered in different browsers. With Google Chrome,

3
00:00:28,630 --> 00:00:38,500
we've got a CC button here, that will enable or disable subtitles. What we can see

4
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:46,020
is that by default the subtitles that are displayed are in German (in this example).

5
00:00:46,020 --> 00:00:54,239
And I can just switch them on and off. It loaded the first track that has the default

6
00:00:54,239 --> 00:01:02,710
attribute. And I have no menu for choosing what track, what language I want to be displayed here …

7
00:01:02,710 --> 00:01:08,210
If we look at FireFox, it's even worse!

8
00:01:08,210 --> 00:01:16,009
We don't have any menu at all, no CC button. I cannot switch on the subtitles, because

9
00:01:16,009 --> 00:01:25,600
as of December 2015, FireFox will load only the first track, if it has the default attribute.

10
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:31,650
This is not the case, so we don't have any subtitles and we cannot display them.

11
00:01:31,650 --> 00:01:38,570
With Safari, on my Mac, it's better because I've got a subtitle menu and I can choose between

12
00:01:38,570 --> 00:01:49,860
